h1. rackup examples

h2. Target version of Rack

* 0.9.1 (gem)
* 0.1 (rackup command)

h2. What is this?

Just write rackup examples.

h3. Run rackup examples

Rackup examples are in the 'config/' directory.
And some applications are in the 'app/' directory.

e.g.
<pre>
[TERM:A] $ cd /path/to/this/clone/directory
[TERM:A] $ rackup config/basic.ru
</pre>
<pre>
[TERM:B] $ curl -v http://user:pass@localhost:9292/
</pre>

h2. Middlewares and Utilities (official)

*NOTE: These category names are unofficial.*

h3. Authentication

* Rack::Auth::Basic
* Rack::Auth::Digest
* Rack::Auth::OpenID

h3. Filter

* Rack::Cascade
* Rack::ConditionalGet
* Rack::ContentLength
* Rack::Deflater
* Rack::ForwardRequest
* Rack::Head
* Rack::MethodOverride
* Rack::Recursive

h3. Serving static contents

* Rack::Directory
* Rack::File
* Rack::Static

h3. Session

* Rack::Session::Cookie
* Rack::Session::Memcache
* Rack::Session::Pool

h3. System

* Rack::CommonLogger
* Rack::Lint
* Rack::Reloader
* Rack::ShowExceptions
* Rack::ShowStatus
* Rack::URLMap

h3. Utilities (Not middleware)

No samples. See official documentation.

* Rack::Mime
* Rack::Utils
* Rack::Utils::Context
* Rack::Utils::HeaderHash
* Rack::Utils::Multipart

h2. Middlewares (contlibutes)

Not supported yet.

